com.capitalone.dashboard.model

Class CollectorItem

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.capitalone.dashboard.model.BaseModel
      • com.capitalone.dashboard.model.CollectorItem
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    CloudConfig, GitHubRepo, JobCollectorItem, ScopeOwner, ScopeOwnerCollectorItem, ScoreCollectorItem, TeamLevelDetails

    public class CollectorItem
extends BaseModel

    Represents a unique collection in an external tool. For example, for a CI tool the collector item would be a Job. For a project management tool, the collector item might be a Scope.

    Each Collector is responsible for specifying how it's CollectorItems are uniquely identified by storing key/value pairs in the options Map. The description field will be visible to users in the UI to aid in selecting the correct CollectorItem for their dashboard. Ideally, the description will be unique for a given Collector.

      • checkErrorOrReset

        public boolean checkErrorOrReset(long resetWindow,
                                 int errorThreshold)
        Checks for collector items error threshold and resets it if window is met
        Parameters:
        resetWindow - - long time in milliseconds after which errors can be reset
        errorThreshold - - number of errors to cross threshold
        Returns:
        true if (a) errors are within threshold and (b) reset if window is passed.
